I"¶<p>Cablegram unnumbered 18 May 1940,</p>

<p>MOST SECRET</p>

<p>With reference to Dominions Office telegram 155 regarding Convoy U.S.3 [1] my telegram raising queries [2] was result of sharp division opinion in War Cabinet.</p>

<p>In view answer now received [3] I am strongly advising Cabinet to agree United Kingdom as ultimate destination but cannot arrange Cabinet Meeting until Tuesday. [4] Understand meanwhile Convoy en route Cape Town.</p>

<p>Please convey foregoing unofficially to United Kingdom Government.</p>

<p>MENZIES</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 Document 252.</p>

<p>2 Document 250.</p>

<p>3 Document 252.</p>

<p>4 21 May 1940.</p>

<p>_</p>

<p><em>[AA: M100, MAY 1940]</em></p>
:ET